[2026-03-05T02:44:54Z] [llm] {"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01NzUBUW3YrwSsMDP6EFT74t","type":"tool_result","content":"     1â†’# Workflows\n     2â†’\n     3â†’Cloche workflows define a directed graph of steps connected by named results.\n     4â†’\n     5â†’## Concepts\n     6â†’\n     7â†’| Concept  | Description                                                        |\n     8â†’|----------|--------------------------------------------------------------------|\n     9â†’| workflow | A named graph of steps connected by result wiring                  |\n    10â†’| step     | A unit of work (inferred: `prompt` = agent, `run` = script)        |\n    11â†’| result   | A named outcome reported by a step (e.g. \"success\", \"fail\")       |\n    12â†’| wiring   | Maps a step's result to the next step                              |\n    13â†’| done     | Built-in terminal step â€” successful completion                     |\n    14â†’| abort    | Built-in terminal step â€” failure with error reporting              |\n    15â†’\n    16â†’## Step Types\n    17â†’\n    18â†’Step type is inferred from the fields present in the step body:\n    19â†’\n    20â†’**agent** (has `prompt`) â€” Invokes a coding agent (Claude Code, or any tool conforming\n    21â†’to the agent adapter interface) with a prompt. The agent works autonomously inside the\n    22â†’container.\n    23â†’\n    24â†’**script** (has `run`) â€” Runs a shell command. Used for tests, linters, validators, or\n    25â†’any deterministic check.\n    26â†’\n    27â†’A step with both `prompt` and `run`, or neither, is a parse error.\n    28â†’\n    29â†’## DSL Syntax\n    30â†’\n    31â†’```\n    32â†’workflow \"implement-feature\" {\n    33â†’  step code {\n    34â†’    prompt = file(\".cloche/prompts/implement.md\")\n    35â†’    container {\n    36â†’      image = \"cloche/agent:latest\"\n    37â†’      network_allow = [\"docs.python.org\"]\n    38â†’    }\n    39â†’    results = [success, fail, retry_with_feedback]\n    40â†’  }\n    41â†’\n    42â†’  step check {\n    43â†’    run = \"make test && make lint\"\n    44â†’    results = [pass, fail]\n    45â†’  }\n    46â†’\n    47â†’  step review {\n    48â†’    prompt = file(\".cloche/prompts/review.md\")\n    49â†’    input = step.code.output\n    50â†’    results = [approved, changes_requested]\n    51â†’  }\n    52â†’\n    53â†’  // Wiring: step:result -> next_step\n    54â†’  code:success -> check\n    55â†’  code:fail -> abort\n    56â†’  code:retry_with_feedback -> code\n    57â†’\n    58â†’  check:pass -> review\n    59â†’  check:fail -> code:retry_with_feedback\n    60â†’\n    61â†’  review:approved -> done\n    62â†’  review:changes_requested -> code\n    63â†’}\n    64â†’```\n    65â†’\n    66â†’## Key Properties\n    67â†’\n    68â†’**Step type is inferred from content.** A `prompt` field makes it an agent step; a `run`\n    69â†’field makes it a script step.\n    70â†’\n    71â†’**Steps declare their possible results.** A step decides at runtime which result to\n    72â†’report. The graph engine follows the wiring to determine the next step.\n    73â†’\n    74â†’**Wiring is separate from step definitions.** This enables inserting new steps between\n    75â†’existing ones by rewiring â€” without modifying either step. This is the foundation for\n    76â†’Cloche's self-evolution feature.\n    77â†’\n    78â†’**Graphs are validated at parse time.** The parser checks that all declared results are\n    79â†’wired, no steps are orphaned, and an entry point exists.\n    80â†’\n    81â†’## Execution Model\n    82â†’\n    83â†’The workflow graph is parsed and executed by `cloche-agent` inside the container.\n    84â†’The agent walks the graph: execute current step, read its result, follow the wiring to\n    85â†’the next step. This continues until a terminal step (`done` or `abort`) is reached.\n    86â†’\n    87â†’All steps in a workflow run inside the same container. File state accumulates naturally\n    88â†’across steps.\n    89â†’"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"cc2e6e8c-da94-4b06-a140-1a3c72b18ec3","uuid":"4dfaa25b-6893-4b87-a0a6-b6f7032db7bf","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/workspace/docs/workflows.md","content":"# Workflows\n\nCloche workflows define a directed graph of steps connected by named results.\n\n## Concepts\n\n| Concept  | Description                                                        |\n|----------|--------------------------------------------------------------------|\n| workflow | A named graph of steps connected by result wiring                  |\n| step     | A unit of work (inferred: `prompt` = agent, `run` = script)        |\n| result   | A named outcome reported by a step (e.g. \"success\", \"fail\")       |\n| wiring   | Maps a step's result to the next step                              |\n| done     | Built-in terminal step â€” successful completion                     |\n| abort    | Built-in terminal step â€” failure with error reporting              |\n\n## Step Types\n\nStep type is inferred from the fields present in the step body:\n\n**agent** (has `prompt`) â€” Invokes a coding agent (Claude Code, or any tool conforming\nto the agent adapter interface) with a prompt. The agent works autonomously inside the\ncontainer.\n\n**script** (has `run`) â€” Runs a shell command. Used for tests, linters, validators, or\nany deterministic check.\n\nA step with both `prompt` and `run`, or neither, is a parse error.\n\n## DSL Syntax\n\n```\nworkflow \"implement-feature\" {\n  step code {\n    prompt = file(\".cloche/prompts/implement.md\")\n    container {\n      image = \"cloche/agent:latest\"\n      network_allow = [\"docs.python.org\"]\n    }\n    results = [success, fail, retry_with_feedback]\n  }\n\n  step check {\n    run = \"make test && make lint\"\n    results = [pass, fail]\n  }\n\n  step review {\n    prompt = file(\".cloche/prompts/review.md\")\n    input = step.code.output\n    results = [approved, changes_requested]\n  }\n\n  // Wiring: step:result -> next_step\n  code:success -> check\n  code:fail -> abort\n  code:retry_with_feedback -> code\n\n  check:pass -> review\n  check:fail -> code:retry_with_feedback\n\n  review:approved -> done\n  review:changes_requested -> code\n}\n```\n\n## Key Properties\n\n**Step type is inferred from content.** A `prompt` field makes it an agent step; a `run`\nfield makes it a script step.\n\n**Steps declare their possible results.** A step decides at runtime which result to\nreport. The graph engine follows the wiring to determine the next step.\n\n**Wiring is separate from step definitions.** This enables inserting new steps between\nexisting ones by rewiring â€” without modifying either step. This is the foundation for\nCloche's self-evolution feature.\n\n**Graphs are validated at parse time.** The parser checks that all declared results are\nwired, no steps are orphaned, and an entry point exists.\n\n## Execution Model\n\nThe workflow graph is parsed and executed by `cloche-agent` inside the container.\nThe agent walks the graph: execute current step, read its result, follow the wiring to\nthe next step. This continues until a terminal step (`done` or `abort`) is reached.\n\nAll steps in a workflow run inside the same container. File state accumulates naturally\nacross steps.\n","numLines":89,"startLine":1,"totalLines":89}}}
